‚úÖ 1. Block Diagram of a Typical 3U VPX Card

Here‚Äôs a high-level block diagram of a generic 3U VPX Single Board Computer (SBC):

+---------------------------------------+
            |           3U VPX Single Board         |
            |                                       |
            |   +-----------------------------+     |
            |   |  Multi-Core CPU / SoC       |     |
            |   |  (Intel Xeon / NXP / ARM)   |     |
            |   +-----------------------------+     |
            |         |               |             |
            |         |               +------------+
            |         |                            |
            |   +-----v-----+                +-----v-----+
            |   | DDR4 RAM  |                | NVMe SSD  |
            |   +-----------+                +-----------+
            |                                       |
            |   +------------------+        +-------v-------+
            |   | PCIe / SRIO /    <--------> Ethernet/10G  |
            |   | High-Speed Switch|        +---------------+
            |   +--------+---------+
            |            |
            |  +---------v------------+
            |  | VPX BACKPLANE        |
            |  | (P0, P1, P2 Conn.)   |
            |  +---------------------+
            |        ||      ||
            |        ||      || GPIO, MIL-STD-1553, etc.
            |   +----++------+------+
            |   |  Custom I/O Module |
            |   +-------------------+
            +---------------------------------------+


