‚úÖ 2. Comparison: 3U VPX vs 6U VPX

Feature	3U VPX	6U VPX

Size	100mm x 160mm	233mm x 160mm
Form Factor	Compact	Larger, more I/O slots
Use Cases	UAVs, small aircraft, satellites	Fighter aircraft, ground systems
Power Consumption	Lower	Higher (can host GPUs, FPGAs)
I/O Capability	Moderate	Extensive I/O and expansion
Chassis Size	Half ATR, 1/4 ATR	Full ATR, 6-slot systems
Typical Slot Use	Mission computer, I/O interface	Signal processing, multi-GPU boards


‚úÖ 3U is preferred in SWaP-constrained applications.


---

‚úÖ 3. Sample VxWorks Software Architecture for 3U VPX SBC

üìå Board: 3U VPX Single Board Computer (SBC)

üìå RTOS: VxWorks 7 / VxWorks 653

üîß Software Layers:

+--------------------------------------------------+
|          APPLICATION LAYER                       |
|  - Mission Management App                        |
|  - Display Controller                            |
|  - Data Link Handler (Link-16 / ARINC 818-2)     |
+--------------------------------------------------+
|          REAL-TIME OPERATING SYSTEM (RTOS)       |
|  - VxWorks 7 Core (microkernel, MM, scheduler)   |
|  - POSIX, FACE, ARINC API support                |
+--------------------------------------------------+
|        BOARD SUPPORT PACKAGE (BSP)               |
|  - CPU Init (NXP QorIQ / Xeon-D / ARM)           |
|  - Device Drivers (Ethernet, SATA, GPIO, USB)    |
|  - PCIe Fabric, VPX Backplane Interfaces         |
+--------------------------------------------------+
|         HARDWARE (3U VPX Card)                   |
|  - CPU + FPGA + Ethernet PHY + Backplane I/O     |
|  - I2C, SPI, UART, MIL-STD-1553, etc.            |
+--------------------------------------------------+


---

‚úÖ Example 3U VPX Deployment in a Mission Computer System

Slot	VPX Card Type	Function

Slot 1	3U SBC (VxWorks)	Mission computer ‚Äì handles MFD, maps, logic
Slot 2	3U FPGA	Real-time radar or sensor processing
Slot 3	3U GPU (NVIDIA or AMD)	Graphics rendering for displays
Slot 4	3U I/O Interface	MIL-STD-1553, ARINC 429, RS-422
Slot 5	3U Data Recorder	NVMe SSD-based flight data logging



---

‚úÖ 4. Software & Middleware Ecosystem (Optional Add-ons)

Layer	Examples

Middleware	DDS (Data Distribution Service), FACE APIs, OpenGL/SC
Security	MILS Separation Kernel (Green Hills, LynxSecure)
Graphics	OpenGL SC for cockpit rendering
Network Stack	TCP/IP, SNMP, ARINC 664
I/O Drivers	MIL-STD-1553, CAN, RS422



---

‚úÖ 5. Standards and Compatibility

Standard	Role

VITA 46	Core VPX electrical & mechanical standard
VITA 48	Cooling: conduction, air, liquid
VITA 65 (OpenVPX)	System slot/module profiles
VITA 66	Optical interconnect (fiber through backplane)
VITA 67	RF coaxial interconnects
CMOSS	Army open systems VPX standard
SOSA	Sensor Open Systems Architecture ‚Äì combines VPX + FACE + CMOSS



---

‚úÖ 6. Real-World Usage of 3U VPX Systems

üõ´ Military Aircraft

LCA Tejas mission computer uses VPX-based computing modules.

Eurofighter and F-35 use VPX for EW and signal processing.


üõ∞Ô∏è Satellites & Space Payloads

Radiation-hardened 3U VPX boards used in low Earth orbit missions.


üöÅ UAV Ground Stations

3U VPX modules used in control computers, video encoders, and telemetry processors.


üõ°Ô∏è Ground Vehicles

Used in C4ISR, battlefield communication, and autonomous control.



